	<div id="p266989" class="post row-fluid even">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=52642&amp;sid=79e69236bcca72a407bafaab304705d1">Tickle</a></strong> &raquo; Tue Jan 22, 2013 3:27 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">BitCoin mining uses GPUs (due to their speed over the CPU), the GPU used in the Raspberry Pi is no where near the speed of the GPUs used in BitCoin mining. I thought about clustering the Pis and creating a bad ass Mining tool but the price and speed was not effective enough to justify clustering. If you want to get into BitCoin mining, research full sized GPUs. <br /><br />My two cents: now that the reward for completion was cut, mining is not worth the electricity cost, or the price of GPUs.</div>

			<div id="sig266989" class="signature">Hunter's Pi Projects:  http://www.hunterthornsberry.com/raspberrypi.html</div>

		</div>

		
